-- Mota-Engil Plans to Reduce Debt by 20% in 3 Years, Sinergia Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-07-31T15:07:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-31/mota-engil-plans-to-reduce-debt-by-20-in-3-years-sinergia-says.html
Mota-Engil SGPS SA (EGL)  plans to cut debt
by about 20 percent in three years to 800 million euros, the
company’s Sinergia magazine reported, citing Chief Financial
Officer Goncalo Moura Martins.  Portugal ’s biggest construction company is available to
sell some of its more mature businesses and invest in other
activities with greater potential for growth, according to the
online version of  Sinergia .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
